    public interface FEVisitor
    Visitor interface for FENode nodes. This class implements part of the "visitor" design pattern for FENodes. The pattern basically exchanges type structures for function calls, so a different function in the visitor is called depending on the run-time type of the object being visited. Calling visitor methods returns some value, the type of which depends on the semantics of the visitor in question. In general, you will create a visitor object, and then pass it to the FENode.accept() method of the object in question.
